docs.lead_paragraph: MONTEVIDEO, Uruguay, June 13--Rogelio Frigerio, often described as a shadowy figure who wields great influence in Argentina, said in an interview here yesterday that his role was a very obvious one--he was a friend of Juan D. Peron, former dictator of Argentina.
docs.abstract: ex-Min Frigerio says he is a friend of Peron and Frondizi and describes his role of trying to unify the forces they represent, int, Montevideo; he and assocs are in exile in Uruguay; he plays key role in talks on formation of pro-Peronist, pro-Frondizi election front; sees election with Peronist participation as only way to end crisis; Govt seeks ruling on whether Lima has violated election law

docs.snippet: WASHINGTON, June 15-- Two Latin-American statesmen recommended today the creation of an inter-American development committee to provide central direction to the limping Alliance for Progress.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, June 15-- Two Latin-American statesmen recommended today the creation of an inter-American development committee to provide central direction to the limping Alliance for Progress.
docs.abstract: Ex-Presidents Kubitschek and Lleras Camargo urge creation of inter-Amer development com to give central direction to Alliance for Progress, repts to OAS Council; Kubitschek charges Alliance is far from meeting ideals proclaimed by Kennedy; notes mistaken US appraisals of other nations; Lleras backs some Kubitschek criticisms; deplores US Cong cut of Alliance funds in '62; says Latin-Amer nations are also responsible for Alliance shortcomings; both deplore lack of central direction in program; US officials disturbed by Kubitschek rept; say US Adm favors multilateral co-op approach
